{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"blurb":"Frontend Engineer @ Qantas. Tinkerer of things. Tea lover. Passionate about react graphql and making things fast."}},"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>I was writing <a href=\"https://github.com/yusinto/ld-vue\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">ld-vue</a> when I needed a way to pass arguments\nto my Vue mixin. In my case, I needed to pass a client id to an external library so it can be\ninitialised. This is the technique I ended up using to pass params to my mixin:</p>\n<h4 id=\"examplemixinjs\"><a href=\"#examplemixinjs\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>exampleMixin.js</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\">\n      <pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> someLibrary <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'some-library'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">exampleMixin</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> clientId <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  methods<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    init<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">      someLibrary<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">initialize</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>clientId<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n</span>    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> exampleMixin</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Instead of defining an object, define a function which returns the mixin object. Pass any\narguments or parameters you want to this function. Then using closure, you can access these\nin your mixin. To use this mixin:</p>\n<h4 id=\"appvue\"><a href=\"#appvue\" aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>App.vue</h4>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\">\n      <pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> exampleMixin <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'./exampleMixin'</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">  mixins<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token function\">exampleMixin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'some-client-id'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>script<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>Call the function with an argument which will generate the <em>real</em> mixin object.</p>\n<hr>","timeToRead":1,"frontmatter":{"date":"September 25, 2018","path":"/vue-mixin-args","title":"Vue Mixins With Arguments","files":[{"name":"hero","publicURL":"/static/hero-1beac63526b0d6d9bbe1299dc722a4a8.png"}],"tags":["vue","mixins","mixin","args","arguments","params","parameters","vuejs","vue2","vuejs2"]}}},"pageContext":{}}